JOS – The Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, Plateau State Chapter, Rufus Bature has felicitated with the Muslim Ummah in Plateau State and Nigeria on the occasion of this year’s Eid-El -Kabir sallah celebrations. Bature in a statement issued in Jos on Saturday and made available to Saturday Independent stated that ” as a festival of sacrifice which Eid-El- Kabir represents, the Chairman calls on all Muslims in the state to rededicate themselves to the preaching of love, peace and brotherliness which are hallmarks of the Holy prophet Mohammed.” He noted that this has become more imparittive at this period when the country is going through grave challenges bordering on terrorism, banditry, kidnapping, attacks on unsuspecting citizens and religious intolerance when we are supposed to be our brothers’ keeper. ‘This year’s celebration coming on the wake of the transition programme, calls for fervent prayers for our country and all those charged with the responsibilities of conducting the 2023 general elections” He added that the peace, progress and unity of our beloved country must not be compromised on the platter of politics which has sadly become our bane. Bature called on all security agents in the state to be vigilant in order to ensure a peaceful and hitch-free salah celebration.